		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The proposed research concerns the further theoretical study of stochastic processes as models of nonequilibrium systems which has applications to many scientific fields.  The central aim of the research is to continue the traditions of studying model systems of different types so that common ground can be determined and general priniciples that relate microscopic processes to macroscopic collective behaviour can be identified.  Specifically I shall investigate new aspects of persistence and coarsening phenomena using the methods I have learned by studying different problems.  Concurrently I shall also work on improving theoretical and numerical methods used to study stochastic processes.  Particularly I aim to develop reliable and generally applicable approximation methods as well as ways in which computer simulations may be made more efficient.The University of Manchester has been selected as the host institution because of the international reputation, expertise and experience of three permanent staff members (Prof. A. J. Bray, Prof. M. A. Moore and Dr A. J. McKane) in the field of stochastic processes.  Through working at Manchester my knowledge of nonequilibrium physics will be considerably broadened due to the fact that the research interests there are markedly different to those of my current institution.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
